#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/xen-guide.xml:200
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"A nice hint is to have the kernel make process store its intermediate object\n"
"files elsewhere so that you can reuse the same kernel tree to build different\n"
"configurations:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/xen-guide.xml:206
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"~# <i>mkdir -p ~/build/dom0 ~/build/domU</i>\n"
"~# <i>make O=~/build/dom0 menuconfig</i>\n"
"<comment>(Configure the kernel)</comment>\n"
"~# <i>make O=~/build/dom0 &amp;&amp; make O=~/build/dom0 modules_install</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/xen-guide.xml:213
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Once the kernel is built you'll find the kernel image immediately in the\n"
"build directory (not inside <path>arch/</path> or any other directory) called\n"
"<path>vmlinuz</path>. Copy it to <path>/boot</path> and then configure your\n"
"bootloader to use the Xen hypervisor (one of the components installed\n"
"previously) which is stored as <path>/boot/xen.gz</path>. In the bootloader\n"
"configuration, add your newly built kernel as the kernel that Xen should\n"
"boot. For instance, for GRUB:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/xen-guide.xml:222
#, no-wrap
msgid "GRUB Configuration for Xen"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/xen-guide.xml:223
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"title Xen 3.0 / Gentoo Linux 2.6.x.y\n"
"root (hd0,0)\n"
"kernel /boot/xen.gz\n"
"module /boot/kernel-2.6.x.y-xen0 root=/dev/sda3\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/xen-guide.xml:230
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Now reboot your system into Xen. Once you are booted, you need to load the Xen\n"
"daemon:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/xen-guide.xml:234
#, no-wrap
msgid "Loading the Xen daemon"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/xen-guide.xml:235
#, no-wrap
msgid "~# <i>/etc/init.d/xend start</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/xen-guide.xml:239
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Now check if you can do whatever you normally do on your system. If this is the\n"
"case, you can edit your bootloader configuration to always boot into Xen and add\n"
"the Xen deamon to the default runlevel so that it is started automatically\n"
"next time you boot.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><note>
#: en/xen-guide.xml:246
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you wish to start guest domains automatically on boot add <c>xendomains</c>\n"
"to the default runlevel as well and create a symlink in\n"
"<path>/etc/xen/auto/</path> to the Xen configuration files for the domains\n"
"you wish to start.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><title>
#: en/xen-guide.xml:256
#, no-wrap
msgid "Creating an Unpriviledged Domain"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/xen-guide.xml:262
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Go to the Xen-powered Linux kernel source and update the configuration. It is\n"
"wise to keep as many topics as possible similar to the main kernel except the\n"
"<c>XEN</c> settings where drivers should now have their <e>frontend</e>\n"
"implementation selected instead of the <e>backend</e>. Then build the kernel\n"
"and place the resulting <path>vmlinuz</path> file where you want (we assume this\n"
"is <path>/mnt/data/xen/kernel</path>):\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/xen-guide.xml:270
#, no-wrap
msgid "Building the guest kernel"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/xen-guide.xml:271
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"~# <i>make O=~/build/domU</i>\n"
"~# <i>cp ~/build/domU/vmlinuz /mnt/data/xen/kernel/kernel-2.6.x.y-xen</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/xen-guide.xml:276
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"It is also possible to create a single kernel image for both the administrative\n"
"domain and the unpriviledged domain. More information about this can be found\n"
"in the Xen user manual.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/xen-guide.xml:284
#, no-wrap
msgid "Creating the Domain Disks"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/xen-guide.xml:288
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"For best performance, it is best to dedicate a partition (or logical volume) to\n"
"a domain rather than a file based filesystem. However, if you are going to use\n"
"Xen primarily for tests using a file based filesystem does have its advantages\n"
"(especially regarding maintenance).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/xen-guide.xml:295
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"You can create a file based filesystem using <c>dd</c> and <c>mke2fs</c> (or\n"
"any other file system creation tool). For instance, to create a 2Gbyte ext3\n"
"filesystem:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/xen-guide.xml:300
#, no-wrap
msgid "Creating a file based filesystem"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/xen-guide.xml:301
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"~# <i>dd if=/dev/zero of=/mnt/data/xen/disks/ext3root.img bs=1M count=2048</i>\n"
"~# <i>mke2fs -j /mnt/data/xen/disks/ext3root.img</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/xen-guide.xml:308
#, no-wrap
msgid "Configuring a Domain"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/xen-guide.xml:312
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Next we create a Xen configuration file for a domain. You can store these\n"
"configuration files where you want, for instance at\n"
"<path>/mnt/data/xen/configs</path>. As an example, we create a configuration\n"
"file for a small Gentoo environment which uses the disk image we created\n"
"previously:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/xen-guide.xml:319
#, no-wrap
msgid "Creating a domain configuration file"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/xen-guide.xml:320
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"~# <i>nano -w /mnt/data/xen/configs/gentoo</i>\n"
"\n"
"kernel = \"/mnt/data/xen/kernel/kernel-2.6.x.y-xen\"\n"
"memory = 512\n"
"name   = \"gentoo\"\n"
"<comment>(Map the disk image to the virtual /dev/sda1)</comment>\n"
"disk   = ['file:/mnt/data/xen/disks/ext3root.img,sda1,w']\n"
"root   = \"/dev/sda1 ro\"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/xen-guide.xml:331
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you are using a block device (such as an lvm volume or partition) for\n"
"the disk use 'phy:' instead of 'file:' and leave off /dev. For example:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/xen-guide.xml:335
#, no-wrap
msgid "Using a block device"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/xen-guide.xml:336
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<comment>(LVM Volume)</comment>\n"
"disk = [ 'phy:lvm/xen-guest-root,sda1,w' ]\n"
"\n"
"<comment>(Physical Partition)</comment>\n"
"disk = [ 'phy:sdb6,sda1,w' ]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/xen-guide.xml:344
#, no-wrap
msgid "You can find example configuration files in <path>/etc/xen</path>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/xen-guide.xml:350
#, no-wrap
msgid "Launching the New Domain"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/xen-guide.xml:354
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Now we're all set and we can launch the new domain. If the disk image contained\n"
"an operating system, we could just create and attach the domain using the\n"
"<c>xm</c> command (Xen manager):\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/xen-guide.xml:359
#, no-wrap
msgid "Creating and starting a new domain"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/xen-guide.xml:360
#, no-wrap
msgid "~# <i>xm create /mnt/data/xen/configs/gentoo -c</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/xen-guide.xml:364
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The domain would be booted inside the terminal in which you executed the\n"
"command. However, in our case, the disk image is empty so the domain won't boot\n"
"up in anything useful. To fix this, you can loop-mount the image and install\n"
"Gentoo as you're used to.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/xen-guide.xml:371
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you want to disconnect from the domain, press <path>Ctrl+]</path>. You can\n"
"always reconnect to the domains' console using <c>xm console gentoo</c>.\n"
"However, there is only one console per domain, so only use it when you can't\n"
"access the domain otherwise (for instance, through SSH).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><title>
#: en/xen-guide.xml:381
#, no-wrap
msgid "Networking on Unpriviledged Domains"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/xen-guide.xml:387
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Xen supports at least two ways of configuring your (virtual) network:\n"
"<e>routed</e> and <e>bridged</e>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/xen-guide.xml:392
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"When selecting the <e>routed</e> approach, the interface inside your\n"
"unpriviledged domain is connected to the virtual interface on your\n"
"administrative domain. On your administrative domain (domain 0), the virtual\n"
"interface is linked together with <path>eth0</path>. The\n"
"interface inside your unpriviledged domain should have an IP address on the same\n"
"network as the interface on the administrative domain. Any communication to\n"
"that IP address can only occur from the administrative domain, unless you set\n"
"up specific routing rules.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/xen-guide.xml:403
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"When selecting the <e>bridged</e> approach, your default network interface on\n"
"the administrative domain becomes a bridge which accepts connections to the\n"
"virtual domains as well as to the IP address your administrative domain has.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/xen-guide.xml:411
#, no-wrap
msgid "Regular Routed Interfaces"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/xen-guide.xml:415
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Before you set up the interface on your unpriviledged domain, make sure that\n"
"Xen's <path>netloop</path> and <path>netbk</path> drivers are loaded. A quick\n"
"hint: if you have <path>netloop</path> as a module, load it with\n"
"<c>nloopbacks=0</c> so that it doesn't create pointless interfaces to the\n"
"loopback device. Then, edit your domain configuration file and add a <c>vif</c>\n"
"instruction to it.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/xen-guide.xml:423 en/xen-guide.xml:479
#, no-wrap
msgid "Configuring a virtual interface"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/xen-guide.xml:424
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"~# <i>nano -w /mnt/data/xen/configs/gentoo</i>\n"
"\n"
"<comment>(Add the vif instruction)</comment>\n"
"vif    = [ 'ip=192.168.1.101, vifname=veth1' ]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/xen-guide.xml:431
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"In the above example, the interface will be created for the unpriviledged domain\n"
"(in which it will be called <path>eth0</path>) and Xen will ensure that address\n"
"192.168.1.101 will be reachable from the administrative domain through interface\n"
"<path>veth1</path>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/xen-guide.xml:438
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"This doesn't mean that the virtual <path>eth0</path> interface will\n"
"automatically have IP 192.168.1.101 assigned to it, but rather that, if you\n"
"don't give it that IP, it will not be connected with the administrative domain\n"
"and thus cannot be reached.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/xen-guide.xml:445
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Now edit <path>/etc/xen/xend-config.sxp</path> as follows to select routed\n"
"network configuration:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/xen-guide.xml:449 en/xen-guide.xml:491
#, no-wrap
msgid "Editing xend-config.sxp"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/xen-guide.xml:450
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"~# <i>nano -w /etc/xen/xend-config.sxp</i>\n"
"\n"
"<comment>(Comment out the following lines)</comment>\n"
"<i>#</i>(network-script network-bridge)\n"
"<i>#</i>(vif-script vif-bridge)\n"
"\n"
"<comment>(Enable the following lines)</comment>\n"
"(network-script network-route)\n"
"(vif-script vif-route)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/xen-guide.xml:464
#, no-wrap
msgid "Bridged Interfaces"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/xen-guide.xml:468
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Unlike the routed interfaces you now need to load the <path>netloop</path>\n"
"driver with <c>nloopbacks=1</c> (or higher) as the additional loopback devices\n"
"are used to create the bridge. For the other modules you still need the\n"
"<path>netbk</path> module as well as briding functionality (<path>bridge</path>\n"
"module if build as such).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/xen-guide.xml:476
#, no-wrap
msgid "Now edit your virtual domain and add the <c>vif</c> construct:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/xen-guide.xml:480
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"~# <i>nano -w /mnt/data/xen/configs/gentoo</i>\n"
"\n"
"<comment>(Add the vif instruction)</comment>\n"
"vif    = [ 'ip=192.168.1.101, vifname=veth0' ]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/xen-guide.xml:487
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Next edit <path>/etc/xen/xend-config.sxp</path> as follows to select bridged\n"
"network configuration:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/xen-guide.xml:492
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"~# <i>nano -w /etc/xen/xend-config.sxp</i>\n"
"\n"
"<comment>(Enable the following lines)</comment>\n"
"(network-script network-bridge)\n"
"(vif-script vif-bridge)\n"
"\n"
"<comment>(Comment out the following lines if not done already)</comment>\n"
"<i>#</i> (network-script network-route)\n"
"<i>#</i> (vif-script vif-route)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/xen-guide.xml:504
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"By default, the bridge will contain whatever interface is configured to be the\n"
"default interface (the device that is listed under the default route through\n"
"<c>ip route list</c>). If you want to alter this behavior, edit the\n"
"<path>xend-config.sxp</path> as follows:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/xen-guide.xml:510
#, no-wrap
msgid "Editing xend-config.sxp to change bridge configuration"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/xen-guide.xml:511
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"~# <i>nano -w /etc/xen/xend-config.sxp</i>\n"
"\n"
"<comment>(Edit the network-script line)</comment>\n"
"(network-script <i>'</i>network-bridge <i>netdev=eth0 bridge=xenbr0 vifnum=0'</i>)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/xen-guide.xml:518
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Once the configuration is done, restart the <c>xend</c> init script to have Xen\n"
"build the bridge:\n"
msgstr ""

